that they turn an eye every now and again

253
00:12:38,319 --> 00:12:40,480
when we're short on bills.

254
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:42,120
It's all in the day's work.

255
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,919
Are you still working?

256
00:12:43,919 --> 00:12:48,919
The shop looks very unkempt and not ready for customers.

257
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:54,600
No, no, haven't been down there in quite some time.

258
00:12:54,639 --> 00:12:55,920
I've been down there just to look,

259
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:58,560
make sure that nobody's walked away with anything.

260
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:00,480
You haven't walked away with anything, have you?

261
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:01,879
Not in a long time.

262
00:13:01,879 --> 00:13:03,120
Not like the last time.

263
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,159
I wasn't fooling you, was I?

264
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:13,600
At first, yeah, you fooled me a little bit.

265
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:18,399
It was the drink that really just kept it from me.

266
00:13:18,399 --> 00:13:21,480
Of course, dulls your senses.

267
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:23,080
You've done well for yourself though.

268
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:27,360
You've, on my back, made it through school and.

269
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:31,320
Oof, you would not have parted with that coin

270
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:34,440
to send me to that school.

271
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,520
No, I wouldn't have.

272
00:13:36,759 --> 00:13:37,560
It's better things to do

273
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:40,280
than waving your magic wands around.

274
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:46,280
You, you don't, you never got it.

275
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:49,160
You never tried to get it.

276
00:13:49,199 --> 00:13:53,799
All you worried about was your hats

277
00:13:53,799 --> 00:13:56,399
and trying to climb a social ladder,

278
00:13:57,799 --> 00:14:01,519
which actually, thinking about it that way,

279
00:14:01,519 --> 00:14:02,839
maybe there's a good reason

280
00:14:02,839 --> 00:14:05,199
for me to come see you after all.

281
00:14:05,199 --> 00:14:06,799
Great, what you got?

282
00:14:07,719 --> 00:14:09,399
You gonna pay back?

283
00:14:09,399 --> 00:14:14,399
Did you have any dealings with a Cressida Thorne?

284
00:14:14,519 --> 00:14:16,639
Lady Thorne, yeah, of course.

285
00:14:16,639 --> 00:14:19,000
We've had dealings with all the nobles in town.

286
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:20,919
They all come here for their hats.

287
00:14:20,919 --> 00:14:22,840
They all need something fancy.

288
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:26,720
Okay, I don't know what I think you can do

289
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:28,000
for me in this regard.

290
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,720
Do you, if I needed,

291
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,919
would you be able to make an introduction?

292
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,159
Wait.

293
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:37,360
Don't.

294
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:39,639
You've come here.

295
00:14:39,639 --> 00:14:40,919
No, I've not come here for this.

296
00:14:40,919 --> 00:14:43,440
I just happened to think about it while I'm here.

297
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:46,320
Okay, you want an introduction to Lady Thorne?

298
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:49,280
If I needed, would you be able to do it?

299
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:51,120
For what reason?

300
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,920
I can introduce you to anybody in town.

301
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,400
Of course I can.

302
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,560
How bad are your financial problems?

303
00:14:56,560 --> 00:15:01,560
He turns his head to the side and things are fine.

304
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:06,960
Your mom's picked up a few extra shifts.

305
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:08,440
And like I said, I haven't been down

306
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:10,880
to make things in a while.

307
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:13,520
But we've got enough favors to pull in

308
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,840
that things are gonna be okay.

309
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,519
So I can get back up on my feet, that is.

310
00:15:18,519 --> 00:15:20,960
You expect to get back up on your feet?

311
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:24,000
Mom made it sound as if any moment

312
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,720
you were going to keel over.

313
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:29,720
Yeah, well, that's one person's opinion, I guess.

314
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:32,879
But I'm really just got a positive outlook

315
00:15:32,879 --> 00:15:34,000
on life these days.

316
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,200
So I'm really just pushing that I'll be in here.

317
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,879
I'm gonna get up right now.

318
00:15:39,879 --> 00:15:43,160
He starts scooting himself over to the edge of the bed

319
00:15:43,319 --> 00:15:46,079
and reaches, pass me that?

320
00:15:46,079 --> 00:15:48,039
Pass me pointing to the crutches?

321
00:15:48,039 --> 00:15:49,360
Do it yourself.

322
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:51,039
No, fine, I got it.

323
00:15:51,039 --> 00:15:54,959
Scoots down to the end of the bed, grabs the crutches

324
00:15:54,959 --> 00:15:57,399
and starts trying to stand up

325
00:15:57,399 --> 00:15:59,879
and like buckles under his own weight.

326
00:15:59,879 --> 00:16:01,480
He's down on one knee now.

327
00:16:02,719 --> 00:16:05,279
Just, I'm getting better.

328
00:16:05,279 --> 00:16:07,360
This is better than it was last week.

329
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:10,959
I step forward and I help him up back onto the bed.

330
00:16:10,959 --> 00:16:11,799
Lie back down.

331
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,400
What'd you come for, Bizard?

332
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,000
I didn't come for this.

333
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:18,040
I just, again, I happened to be here

334
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:20,240
and I don't know.

335
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:23,880
I stopped by and saw Mom at the cured pig.

336
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:26,560
Was surprised to see and hear how much she was working

337
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,120
in your state.

338
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:33,120
And honestly, I don't know why Mom stays with you.

339
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,760
I've offered to have her come

340
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:37,960
and stay with me in Vintersmouth

341
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:40,240
and whatever happens to you, happens to you.

342
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:41,560
I don't think she'll do it.

343
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:43,560
And I don't understand why.

344
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:48,560
The only thing, you cared so much for your status,

345
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:52,920
the people you made hats for

346
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:57,200
and those relationships that you ignored

347
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:59,640
the relationships in your own home.

348
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:00,560
Did you provide for us?

349
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:01,440
Yeah, sure.

350
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,400
I'll give you that.

351
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:05,400
You provided for us.

352
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,440
You made sure that we had food and house.

353
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:11,200
But you weren't there in many ways.

354
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:17,359
And I don't know if I can afford you the same grace

355
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:25,119
of just not being there, but helping out financially.

356
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:28,279
But if Mom doesn't go with me,

357
00:17:28,279 --> 00:17:29,159
well, you maybe already know

358
00:17:29,159 --> 00:17:30,960
that I've been sending her money.

359
00:17:32,079 --> 00:17:35,519
But I don't want her working anymore.

360
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:40,079
And if it means having to give her money

361
00:17:40,079 --> 00:17:42,720
to help take care of you, I will do it for her.

362
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:45,519
Do you have any medications I need to give you?

363
00:17:45,519 --> 00:17:47,039
Like, you know, I can.

364
00:17:47,039 --> 00:17:52,039
No, no, I don't want to put you out, I'm fine.

365
00:17:52,039 --> 00:17:55,000
No, you sound like you were coughing here.

366
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,119
I get you a glass of water

367
00:17:57,119 --> 00:18:02,119
and I grab a glass, go over to fill it up.

368
00:18:02,119 --> 00:18:04,559
And I'm just kind of like, you know,

369
00:18:04,559 --> 00:18:05,519
trying to capture myself.

370
00:18:05,519 --> 00:18:09,319
I'm like at the counter with the water filling up.

371
00:18:09,319 --> 00:18:10,759
And I'm just kind of staring into the water

372
00:18:10,759 --> 00:18:12,639
as it fills the glass.

373
00:18:12,639 --> 00:18:16,960
And for a moment, I reach into my like breast pocket

374
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:20,319
and reaching for like a handkerchief.

375
00:18:20,319 --> 00:18:23,119
But then I feel a small vial

376
00:18:23,119 --> 00:18:27,039
and I stop and like thumb the lid of it for a second

377
00:18:28,079 --> 00:18:31,799
and just kind of like mile long stare.

378
00:18:34,159 --> 00:18:36,279
Pull my hand out of my pocket, shake it off,

379
00:18:36,319 --> 00:18:39,680
turn the water off and bring him the glass of water back.

380
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,519
And I set it down.

381
00:18:40,519 --> 00:18:44,200
I say, one thing that you taught me

382
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:48,680
that I am so, so grateful for.

383
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:53,160
One thing that makes me semi-okay

384
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:55,879
with you being my dad is that you taught me

385
00:18:55,879 --> 00:18:58,119
the kind of person I don't want to be.

386
00:18:59,119 --> 00:19:01,399
So thank you so, so much.

387
00:19:01,399 --> 00:19:03,200
And I will pay you back.

388
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:06,079
In fact, I don't want to owe you anything.

389
00:19:06,919 --> 00:19:10,079
And I pull out a cashier's check.

390
00:19:10,079 --> 00:19:12,759
And over the last 10 years,

391
00:19:12,759 --> 00:19:15,439
not having to pay taxes out in Vintersmouth,

392
00:19:15,439 --> 00:19:20,000
I've managed to scrape and save aside 800 gold per year.

393
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,480
Over 10 years is 8,000 gold,

394
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:25,720
which is four years tuition at Barnhart's.

395
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:28,039
I write it down and I say,

396
00:19:28,039 --> 00:19:32,240
I'm gonna give this to mom to take care of both of you.

397
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:35,519
That is if she doesn't leave with me.

398
00:19:35,559 --> 00:19:36,799
And if she does,

399
00:19:36,799 --> 00:19:40,160
I hope you can call on those favors as you need

400
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:43,480
and do what you need to take care of the rest of your life.

401
00:19:45,039 --> 00:19:45,879
Are you done?

402
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:48,079
Are we done?

403
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:50,240
Yeah.

404
00:19:51,799 --> 00:19:54,200
You got everything off your chest that you need?

405
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:56,319
Yeah.

406
00:19:57,519 --> 00:20:00,639
Do you have anything you wanna get off your chest with me?

407
00:20:00,639 --> 00:20:03,480
Anything you wanna say that you never said?

408
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:08,480
Stares at you for a long, uncomfortable moment.

409
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:12,480
I wish I would have called you out.

410
00:20:14,039 --> 00:20:17,400
Taking my money, going off to your wizard school.

411
00:20:18,759 --> 00:20:20,759
Maybe you would have came to make a hat.

412
00:20:20,759 --> 00:20:23,680
Maybe you would have done something valuable.

413
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:27,279
I don't have anything to say, kid.

414
00:20:28,680 --> 00:20:31,160
I'll talk to your mother tonight.

415
00:20:31,160 --> 00:20:33,160
Sounds like she has a decision to make.

416
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:35,000
I would say so.

417
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:37,519
Thank you.

418
00:20:37,519 --> 00:20:39,559
Odd as it is to say it.

419
00:20:39,559 --> 00:20:40,400
I guess mom was right.

420
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,839
It was good that I came here

421
00:20:41,839 --> 00:20:45,240
cause I'm proud of what I'm doing

422
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:48,799
and I don't need validation from you.

423
00:20:48,799 --> 00:20:49,640
Good.

424
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:50,480
And I've realized that.

425
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:52,279
Well, another thing I taught you then.

426
00:20:53,519 --> 00:20:58,319
I just kind of like sigh and turn and walk out the door,

427
00:20:58,319 --> 00:21:01,960
hand in my breast pocket again, thumb in that vial.

428
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,519
I walk downstairs.

429
00:21:03,519 --> 00:21:05,200
I pick up my pack.

430
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,720
I take my key.

431
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:10,039
I put it on the counter, lock the door behind me.

432
00:21:10,039 --> 00:21:11,960
I'm gonna go sit in a park

433
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:15,200
and think back on what the divining teacher told me

434
00:21:16,279 --> 00:21:18,920
and try to piece together the parts of it.

435
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:22,799
We'll be right back.

436
00:21:22,799 --> 00:21:25,079
It's the middle.

437
00:21:25,079 --> 00:21:28,120
I mean, nothing against making a golem for yourself,

438
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,200
like a holiday golem.

439
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,840
Sure, yeah.

440
00:21:30,879 --> 00:21:33,319
We're basically seeing like,

441
00:21:33,319 --> 00:21:34,159
what is that?

442
00:21:34,159 --> 00:21:37,039
Conjuration, transmutation, magic at work.

443
00:21:37,039 --> 00:21:40,319
But you may as well do it all

444
00:21:40,319 --> 00:21:42,599
so he can give you the hot frosty.

445
00:21:42,599 --> 00:21:43,959
Yeah.

446
00:21:43,959 --> 00:21:44,799
Yeah.

447
00:21:44,799 --> 00:21:46,079
It's really what it comes down to.

448
00:21:46,079 --> 00:21:49,759
What's the point of even having a snowman come to life?

449
00:21:49,759 --> 00:21:51,559
Welcome to the middle, everybody.

450
00:21:51,559 --> 00:21:53,359
Oh shit, we started recording.

451
00:21:53,359 --> 00:21:54,879
I know, we're well into it.

452
00:21:54,879 --> 00:21:56,679
I was too busy looking at all the pictures

453
00:21:56,679 --> 00:21:58,159
of hot frosty.

454
00:21:58,240 --> 00:22:00,519
Yeah, no, that's the big movie

455
00:22:00,519 --> 00:22:01,800
that we're talking about this year

456
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:04,240
is Hot Frosty, not a sponsor.

457
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,080
We just talk about it

458
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:07,360
because we love it so gosh darn much.

459
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,680
Or maybe we will.

460
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:09,519
Maybe we will.

461
00:22:09,519 --> 00:22:11,400
I mean, two of the five have seen it,

462
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,960
three have not.

463
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:13,800
Yeah.

464
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,360
Of course, it's only on Netflix, right.

465
00:22:15,360 --> 00:22:17,519
Okay, that makes a lot more sense.

466
00:22:17,519 --> 00:22:19,640
Maybe better than Hot Frosty.

467
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:20,480
Almost certainly.

468
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:22,200
I don't even know what you're gonna say, but.

469
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,040
Yeah.

470
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:26,840
Is our Christmas special, which comes out next week.

471
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,559
Oh, that's right.

472
00:22:28,559 --> 00:22:29,399
Yeah.

473
00:22:29,399 --> 00:22:30,240
Very true.

474
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,519
Folks, I can't even explain.

475
00:22:32,519 --> 00:22:34,839
Like is it just us laughing?

476
00:22:34,839 --> 00:22:35,679
Yes, that is the entire special.

477
00:22:35,679 --> 00:22:37,159
With no other words coming out,

478
00:22:37,159 --> 00:22:38,519
I feel like it might be wonderful.

479
00:22:38,519 --> 00:22:39,799
Yeah.

480
00:22:39,799 --> 00:22:42,439
Of just like one liner and then laughing

481
00:22:42,439 --> 00:22:45,199
and followed by another zinger and then laughing.

482
00:22:45,199 --> 00:22:46,199
Yeah. Perfect.

483
00:22:46,199 --> 00:22:47,119
Just the way we do.

484
00:22:47,119 --> 00:22:48,399
It was a delight.

485
00:22:48,399 --> 00:22:49,240
Yeah. It was a great time.

486
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:50,079
Really, really fun.

487
00:22:50,079 --> 00:22:51,879
It was a lot of fun to get to run

488
00:22:51,879 --> 00:22:55,480
and it was everything I could never expect it to be.

489
00:22:55,519 --> 00:22:58,799
I don't know how much I wanna tell you.

490
00:22:58,799 --> 00:22:59,640
Like we should tease it in the middle.

491
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:00,480
I said nothing.

492
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:01,319
Don't say anything.

493
00:23:01,319 --> 00:23:02,440
I mean, you already gave a teaser

494
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,599
with something you said a moment ago.

495
00:23:04,599 --> 00:23:05,440
That's true.

496
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:07,720
You gotta really pay attention to words

497
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,440
and then look back on things, but you know.

498
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:10,279
Yeah, well, nobody else.

499
00:23:10,279 --> 00:23:12,039
Well, there's no way people can hit rewind

500
00:23:12,039 --> 00:23:13,279
and listen again, so.

501
00:23:13,279 --> 00:23:14,120
Nope.

502
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:17,680
You won't know which words Kyle's talking about.

503
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:19,440
So, I mean, who knows.

504
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,920
Who knows anything.

505
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:22,319
But what we can tell you is

506
00:23:22,319 --> 00:23:24,880
we have a wonderful guest, Abdul Aziz,

507
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:26,120
who's come to join us again

508
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:30,240
to help us ring in the new year and holiday season.

509
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:31,560
Nothing to do with the new year,

510
00:23:31,560 --> 00:23:33,520
but definitely to do with the holiday season.

511
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:34,640
We all made a face.

512
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:35,480
I was so thrown off.

513
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:36,320
Do we?

514
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:37,160
I was like, did I black out?

515
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:38,760
We didn't do anything about the new year.

516
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:41,840
Yeah, in fact, the whole episode is a new year special.

517
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:42,680
Yeah.

518
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:43,520
Oh my gosh.

519
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,360
Was I there?

520
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:45,200
